President Obama has announced the appointment of several individuals to key administration posts. Margaret Murnane has been appointed as Chairman of the President's Committee on the National Medal of Science. She is a Fellow of JILA and a Distinguished Professor at the University of Colorado. Judith Kimble has been appointed as a Member of the President's Committee on the National Medal of Science. She is the Vilas Professor of Biochemistry at the University of Wisconsin-Madison. Henry T. Yang has also been appointed as a Member of the President's Committee on the National Medal of Science. He is the Chancellor of the University of California, Santa Barbara. Beth White has been appointed as a Member of the National Capital Planning Commission. She is the Director of the Chicago Region Office of The Trust for Public Land. Susan York has been appointed as a Member of the Commission for the Preservation of America's Heritage Abroad. She serves on the board of directors of Women in Need and directs fundraising for Marymount and Browning schools.